
1. What is an Inventory Management System (IMS)?
→ An IMS is a software tool used to track, manage, and control stock levels, orders, sales, and deliveries. It helps optimize inventory, reduce overstocking, and prevent stockouts.


2. What are the key components of an Inventory Management System?

Product details (SKU, category, description)

Stock tracking

Supplier & purchase management

Sales & order tracking

Reports & analytics



3. Why is inventory management important for a business?
→ It ensures products are available when needed, reduces holding costs, prevents wastage, and improves cash flow.


